SessionDuration bounds (Minimum=900, Maximum=43200) come directly from AWS
admission validation for AssumeRole and AssumeRoleWithWebIdentity:
- 900s (15 min) is the AWS minimum for any role session
- 43200s (12 h) is the AWS absolute ceiling regardless of role configuration
These were added as kubebuilder markers so the CRD rejects out-of-range
values at admission time instead of at STS API call time.

MFA was already defined as GeneratorKindMFA and in GeneratorSpec but had
been accidentally omitted from the kubebuilder:validation:Enum annotation,
causing the CRD to reject ClusterGenerator.spec.kind: MFA. Fixed here since
the enum line was already being touched to add STSAssumeRoleToken.
